A CoProduction between HOUSE OF TALKIES (A Story Ink Company) and ENDEMOL SHINE INDIA for NETFLIX, we bring to you the most compelling story of the year - #TrialByFire. 

#HouseOfTalkies is a production company founded by Sidharth Jain of #TheStoryInk. This is our first #BookToScreen Project to stream on your screen.

13 June, 1997 altered the lives of hundreds of families. #TrialByFire traces the story of parents, Neelam and Shekhar Krishnamoorthy, who alongside other families have fought for justice. Catch their story in #TrialByFire, releasing January 13 only on @netflix_in

Our philosophy at #TheStoryInk has always been to expand the ecosystem of #stories and #storytellers. 

To achieve that, we got into our fold 250+ #authors and enabled sale of 200+ book-to-screen rights to 50+ #producers in just 5 years.

To further expand the premium video content ecosystem, we need to bring into the ecosystem, new and emerging screen writers. This will enable successful collaborations leading to higher quality of writing, lower cost of development and ease of deal closure. 

Two goals - 
1. Make it easy for a producer to walk into #TheStoryInk, find a story and a team of writers for development of a bible or a script at an affordable cost, and easy commercial + legal deal closure.
2. New, emerging and deserving writers will get a platform where they will be mentored and given opportunities, which will help them build a stable and long term career.

Hence, presenting #TheStoryInkTalent. Talent that we represent will not only get a chance to work on projects by #HouseOfTalkies (Trial by Fire) but will have access to our Producer and Studio Network.

For More details - link in bio or www.TheStoryInk.com

#OnceUponATime when #Hollywood came to #bollywood - super retro #throwback to my first film as a #producer with #SalmanKhan. I was young & restless. A 5 country #coproduction #film in English - “Marigold”. The timing was wrong and valuable lessons learnt. Rachel Saltz of #TheNewYorkTimes rated the film 4 out of 5, stating ″ Mr. Carroll knows his Bollywood stuff and, refreshingly, doesn’t apologize for, or waste time explaining, an industry and a style that most Americans still regard as silly. Instead, he honors them.″[6] Conversely, Kirk Honeycutt of The #HollywoodReporter gave a negative review, writing ″The film will suffer on two fronts: Bollywood fans will dismiss the mishmash as the work of an American director “slumming” in a genre outside his own culture, and Western audiences unfamiliar with Hindi-language masala movies will find the whole thing puzzling.″ The film had @alilarter in the lead role with @beingsalmankhan and was directed by Willard Carroll who had made the @miramax film #PlayingByHeart starring #SeanConnery, #AngelinaJolie, #DennisQuaid #GillianAnderson #RyanPhillipe #JonStewart #GenaRowlands #MadeleineStowe & #JayMohr

Since 2018, we at #TheStoryInk, have been representing countless Books, Scripts and stories for Screen Adaptation.

We feel it’s time we optimise our resources and sharpen the focus for better results for you.

To best assist you - our writers and storytellers - and represent your work for screen, we are now excited to announce our new submission process which includes two plans - Silver and Gold. 

Both these plans focus on a detailed action plan to represent and pitch your story to the world and get it the attention it deserves.

For any material you wish to pitch to us, please choose the plan you think works best for you. As always, we look forward to being a part of your book to screen journey.

Past submissions and representations won’t be affected with these new plans.

Calling all writers! 📖📽️✒️

The Story Ink is partnering with us through October for the First Draft Club #15. 

The Story Ink is India's #1 book-to-screen agency, so we will talk books, scripts, screenplays, and more. 

The First Draft Club (FDC) is a writing community that helps you write more, write better.

How does FDC work?
✒️Make a donation of INR 750 (more is welcome) to the Chirag School, a unique NGO-run school in the rural Himalayas.
✒️Join a writing community of 100+ writers. Exchange prompts, feedback, and motivation. Update your daily word count in our word count tracker, and track your progress.
✒️Every Sunday e-meet a literary expert from The Story Ink and learn from their journey.

Do some good, meet your writing goals, and e-meet industry experts. It's a win-win-win!

The best part? You never have to write alone again.

Stay tuned for the list of filmy experts!

Meet acclaimed @the_story_ink experts this October in the First Draft Club.

Sidharth has been working as a Producer in the Indian Entertainment Industry for 20+ years.

He Founded The Story Ink in 2018 and it is now India's Largest Book to Screen Adaptation Company, having set up 200+ books across 50+ Production Houses. The Story Ink represents 250+ Authors and exclusively controls the screen rights of more than 500 books. 

In 2021 Sidharth founded a development and production company - @houseoftalkies, which has a multi-format slate of film & series projects. The first series project commissioned by Netflix - Trial By Fire - launched on 13th January, 2023. The show is about two parents' fight for justice after the Uphaar cinema tragedy.

During The Story Ink FDC #15 we'll host him for an hour-long Zoom chat at 5 PM on Sunday, the 1st of October. Other The Story Ink FDC Experts include Leena Yadav, Anirban Bhattacharyya, Atika Chohan, and Nikhil Sachan.

Chat with these experts, and get your writing going this October.
